<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41038c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41038c">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41038c"> 38(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> restraint on / anticipation</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Equity allowed a married woman to deal as she pleased with her separate estate, either by deed during her lifetime or by her will, unless her interest in it was subject to <mark>restraint on anticipation</mark>. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 35</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
